  description: "struct.error.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('Exception') == True — 'Exception' (9 chars; struct.error inherits directly from Exception — the standard base class for non-fatal errors in Python; __bases__[0].__name__=='Exception' confirms the immediate base class; struct.error's MRO is (struct.error, Exception, BaseException, object) — 4 classes total (struct_extra168 anchors error.__mro__.__len__()==4); 'Exception'(9) is the longest name in this spec: 'pack'(4) < 'error'(5) < 'Struct'(6) < '_struct'(7) < 'calcsize'(8) < 'Exception'(9); struct_extra161 anchors error.__bases__[0].__name__=='Exception' as a table row; this spec provides a fresh standalone anchor under structclass169; first structclass169 standalone for error.__bases__[0].__name__.__eq__('Exception')"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
