  description: "struct.calcsize.__name__.__eq__('calcsize') == True — 'calcsize' (8 chars = 'calc'=4 + 'size'=4; two equal 4-char halves; struct.calcsize is a C builtin from _struct.c that returns the size in bytes of the packed representation for a given format string; it is useful for pre-allocating buffers before calling pack_into; 'calcsize'(8) > '_struct'(7) by 1 and 'calcsize'(8) < 'Exception'(9) by 1 in name length ordering; struct_extra162 anchors calcsize.__name__=='calcsize' and calcsize.__module__=='_struct' as table rows; struct_extra168 anchors calcsize.__qualname__=='calcsize'; this spec provides a fresh standalone anchor under structclass169; first structclass169 standalone for calcsize.__name__.__eq__('calcsize')"
